com.citytechinc.cq.component.annotations

Annotation Type DialogFieldOverride


  • @Retention(value=CLASS)
@Target(value={FIELD,METHOD})
public @interface DialogFieldOverride
    The DialogFieldOverride annotation is used to override settings from a DialogField annotation on an interface or overriden method.

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      boolean hideLabel
      Used to set the hideLabel widget property in the dialog.
      boolean required
      Indicates that population of the widget input in the dialog is required.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      Property[] additionalProperties
      A list of additional properties not already represented by properties of the annotation.
      String cssClass
      For Touch-UI Only Additional css classes to attribute to the rendered field
      String defaultValue
      Used to set the defaultValue widget property in the dialog.
      boolean disabled
      For Touch-UI Only Indicates that the particular field should be rendered in a disabled state
      String fieldDescription
      Populates the fieldDescription widget property in the dialog.
      String fieldLabel
      The human-readable label for the input field which will be presented in a dialog.
      Listener[] listeners
      The set of listeners which will be attributed to the dialog widget associated with the authorable element.
      boolean mergeAdditionalProperties
      If this is set to true, the instead of overriding the additional properties, the additional properties from the parent will be merged with the ones from this annotation.
      boolean mergeLiseners
      If this is set to true, the instead of overriding the listeners, the listeners from the parent will be merged with the ones from this annotation.
      String name
      The path to which the value for the authorable element will be saved during content authoring.
      double ranking
      Used to order dialog widgets within a tab.
      boolean suppressTouchUI
      Indicates that a Touch UI widget should not be produced for the annotated member
      int tab
      The index number, starting at 1, of the tab in which to place the dialog widget representing this authorable element.
      String title
      For Touch-UI Only
      String value
      For Touch-UI Only Many of the Touch UI widgets react to an underlying value being set for the field.

    • Element Detail

      • required

        public abstract boolean required
        Indicates that population of the widget input in the dialog is required. Used to set the allowBlank widget property in the dialog. Unlike DialogField this is required because we can't default to the value set on DialogField
        Returns:
        boolean

      • hideLabel

        public abstract boolean hideLabel
        Used to set the hideLabel widget property in the dialog. Unlike DialogField this is required because we can't default to the value set on DialogField
        Returns:
        boolean

      • additionalProperties

        public abstract Property[] additionalProperties
        A list of additional properties not already represented by properties of the annotation. Each additional property is output as a widget property in the dialog.
        Returns:
        FieldProperty[]
        Default:
        {}

      • mergeAdditionalProperties

        public abstract boolean mergeAdditionalProperties
        If this is set to true, the instead of overriding the additional properties, the additional properties from the parent will be merged with the ones from this annotation.
        Default:
        false

      • listeners

        public abstract Listener[] listeners
        The set of listeners which will be attributed to the dialog widget associated with the authorable element. Listeners are output as properties in the listeners XML node which is a child of the XML node representing the widget in the dialog.
        Returns:
        Listener[]
        Default:
        {}

      • mergeLiseners

        public abstract boolean mergeLiseners
        If this is set to true, the instead of overriding the listeners, the listeners from the parent will be merged with the ones from this annotation.
        Default:
        false

      • ranking

        public abstract double ranking
        Used to order dialog widgets within a tab. Widgets representing authorable elements with a higher ranking appear lower in the tab than elements with a lower ranking. The ordering of elements of equal ranking is not guaranteed.
        Returns:
        double
        Default:
        0.0
